  "informal_statement": "If g is a left inverse of f (g(f(x)) = x for all x), then f is injective.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Suppose f a = f b. Apply g to both sides to get g(f a) = g(f b), then rewrite both sides using the left-inverse equations g(f a) = a and g(f b) = b to conclude a = b.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem left_inverse_injective (α β : Type) (f : α → β) (g : β → α) (h : Function.LeftInverse g f) : Function.Injective f",
