  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode 05445672), kernel_verified on the first attempt. This domain's `README.md` lists 'inverse' as an explicit focus item alongside injective/surjective/composition/monotone/fixed-point/image-preimage, but until this packet nothing in the domain touched `Function.LeftInverse`/`RightInverse` at all -- confirmed via `grep -rl LeftInverse\\|RightInverse packets/elementary/functions/*.json` (no hits) before authoring. Proved directly from the definition (`congrArg g hab` then rewriting via the two left-inverse equations) rather than citing a Mathlib convenience lemma by name, since `mathlib_search_declarations` results for `LeftInverse.injective` were noisy/ambiguous (many unrelated `injective` hits from other namespaces) -- the from-scratch two-line proof sidesteps needing to pin down the exact current Mathlib name. `general_amgm`/`am_hm_two`-style domain-tagged `algebra` per this folder's established convention (schema has no `functions` domain value).",
